# Compiler design overview

Beanstalk's compiler is a staged frontend with a builder-owned backend handoff. The frontend turns source files into validated HIR and borrow facts. Project builders assemble backend-specific artifacts from those compiled modules.

These pages record accepted compiler architecture and intended end-state contracts. They include design decisions that may not yet be fully implemented.

They are not an implementation-status report. Use `docs/src/docs/progress/#page.bst` for current support, partial coverage, experimental paths and major gaps.

