## Cross-cutting design documents

- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/build-system-and-frontend-boundary/build-system-and-frontend-boundary.bd`: `BackendBuilder`, `BuilderSurface`, config compilation and source-file kinds
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/diagnostics-paths-and-symbols/diagnostics-paths-and-symbols.bd`: `CompilerDiagnostic`, `CompilerError`, `StringTable`, source locations and style directives
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/type-identity-and-coercion/type-identity-and-coercion.bd`: `TypeEnvironment`, `TypeId`, `DataType` and contextual coercion
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/imports-packages-and-bindings/imports-packages-and-bindings.bd`: source-backed packages, binding-backed packages, module public surfaces, provider imports and visibility
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/entry-start-and-page-fragments/entry-start-and-page-fragments.bd`: implicit `start`, const/runtime fragment split and builder-owned fragment assembly
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/parallelism-and-determinism/parallelism-and-determinism.bd`: string-table merge, parallel inventory and serial AST emission
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/ast/overview.bd`: environment, expressions, constants, templates and generics
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/backend/overview.bd`: validation, HTML assembly, JS, Wasm, external JS and tracked assets
- `docs/src/docs/codebase/memory-management/overview.bd`: GC baseline, shared access, borrow validation, ownership and backend lowering

## Non-negotiable contracts

- Header parsing discovers top-level declarations once. AST consumes sorted headers and header-built visibility.
- Semantic type identity is `TypeId` equality in the active `TypeEnvironment`.
- User failures use `CompilerDiagnostic`. Internal invariant failures use `CompilerError`.
- HIR is the first backend-facing semantic IR.
- Generics, traits and cast evidence resolve before HIR.
- AST finishes template semantics before HIR lowers runtime templates.
- Borrow validation reads HIR and produces side tables without rewriting HIR.
- GC remains the semantic baseline.
- Backends do not reinterpret source syntax.
- Parallelism must preserve deterministic identity and diagnostics.
